## Technical Architecture

### Infrastructure (AWS)

- **Frontend:** AWS Amplify (Next.js 15 micro-frontends)
- **Backend:** AWS EC2 with PM2 (Fastify API, port 4003)
- **Database:** AWS RDS PostgreSQL (primary) + DynamoDB (audit/API logs, metrics)
- **Cache:** Redis/Valkey (sessions, caching)
- **Storage:** AWS S3 (documents)
- **Monitoring:** Sentry (errors, performance)
- **Deployment:** CodePipeline/CodeDeploy (test/stage/production)

### Architecture Patterns

- **Hybrid Micro-Frontend:** Host app (Next.js 15 App Router) + remote modules (Pages Router + Module Federation) via RemoteLoader
- **Class-Based Backend with DI:** Controller-Service-Repository pattern with dependency injection
- **Layered Separation:** Controller (HTTP only) → Service (business logic, logging, audit) → Repository (data access, silent)
- **BFF Pattern:** Next.js API routes as proxy layer (CSRF/security, no business logic)
- **Modular Prisma Schemas:** Split into work package files (wp1-main-contract.prisma, etc.) with auto-discovery
- **Git-Based Package Distribution:** Shared auth (@myerp/auth) via Git dependency, internal packages via workspace protocol
- **Dual Logging:** Winston (structured) + DynamoDB (audit trails) + Sentry (errors)

### Database Design

- **Multi-tenancy:** Row-level with tenantId on every table
- **Separate DBs per app group:** Core (Procurement, Shell, HR), Commercial, Site Management, etc.
- **Soft Delete:** All entities have deletedAt (never hard delete)
- **Mandatory Indexes:** tenantId, deletedAt, createdAt
- **Audit Fields:** createdAt, createdBy, updatedAt, updatedBy, deletedAt, deletedBy
- **Tenant Isolation:** EVERY query filters by tenantId AND deletedAt: null (enforced at repository layer)
- **DynamoDB:** Audit logs, API logs, error logs (no ACID requirements)
- **ORM:** Prisma with modular schema organization, singleton client, connection pooling

### Tech Stack

- Next.js 15, TypeScript
- Fastify (backend API)
- Prisma, PostgreSQL, DynamoDB
- Tailwind CSS
- JWT authentication
- TurboRepo (monorepo)

